ANNE MCELVOY asks Melinda Gates, an American philanthropist, whether gender equality starts in the home. Mrs Gates explains why the tech world risks entrenching biases, and defends the Gates Foundation’s decision to halve its paid family leave. And Ms McElvoy and Mrs Gates swap top tips for getting teenagers to do the washing up. Runtime: 20 min    Listen on: Apple Podcasts | Spotify | Google | Stitcher | TuneIn